Opportunity Zones in Fairfax County, VA

Teja Pristavec

November 28, 2019

For this task, we want to visualize all opportunity zones in Fairfax County and their neighboring tracts. Opportunity zones are select low-income Census tracts eligible for investment incentives, and there are nine within Fairfax County, VA.

1 Getting the data

Our first step is to request Fairfax County geography from tigris. We look for tracts in Virginia, and for county Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS) code 059. We convert the object to a simple feature (sf).

library(tigris)
library(sf)

ffxcounty <- tracts("VA", county = "059", progress_bar = FALSE)
ffxcounty <- st_as_sf(ffxcounty)

2 Identifying tracts of interest

Now that we have information on all tracts, we also want to create an indicator for opportunity zones, our tracts of interest. There are nine in Fairfax County, VA (North Hill, Hybla Valley, Mount Vernon Woods, South County Center, Willston Center, Baileys North/Glen Forest, Skyline Plaza, Herndon South, and Lake Anne), and their numbers are 4810, 4821, 4514, 4515.02, 4528.01, 4154.01, 4215, 4216, and 4218.

library(dplyr)

ffxcounty <- ffxcounty %>% mutate(opportunity = ifelse((NAME == 4810 |
                                                        NAME == 4821 |
                                                        NAME == 4514 |
                                                        NAME == 4515.02 |
                                                        NAME == 4528.01 |
                                                        NAME == 4154.01 |
                                                        NAME == 4215 |
                                                        NAME == 4216 |
                                                        NAME == 4218), 1, 0))

Well also need to identify neighboring tracts to compare with opportunity zones. We create an object with our zones only, and then use st_touches to select tracts that share any zones border. st_touches gives the result as a list, so we unlist it.

# Identify zone neighbors
zones <- ffxcounty %>% filter(opportunity == 1)

neighbors <- st_touches(zones, ffxcounty, sparse = TRUE)
neighborlist <- unlist(neighbors)

# Create neighbor indicator
ffxcounty <- ffxcounty %>% mutate(id = row_number(),
                                  neighbor = ifelse(id %in% neighborlist, 1, 0))

3 Plotting zones and neighbors

Having defined our variables, we work on plotting. First, we make a test plot to make sure were on the right track, and convert variables to factors so theyll be easier to work with later.

# Test plot again with all indicators in same dataset
plot(st_geometry(ffxcounty), col = "white")
plot(st_geometry(ffxcounty[ffxcounty$neighbor == 1, ]), add = TRUE, col = "blue")
plot(st_geometry(ffxcounty[ffxcounty$opportunity == 1, ]), add = TRUE, col = "red")

# Convert to factor
ffxcounty$neighbor <- as.factor(ffxcounty$neighbor)
ffxcounty$opportunity <- as.factor(ffxcounty$opportunity)

With our prototype done, we put some effort into aesthetics. Before plotting, we need assign coordinates for our zone labels.

# Select tracts
labelzones <- ffxcounty[ffxcounty$opportunity == 1, ]
labelneighbors <- ffxcounty[ffxcounty$neighbor == 1, ]

# Get points
point_zones <- st_point_on_surface(labelzones)
point_neighbors <- st_point_on_surface(labelneighbors)

# Retrieve coordinates
coords_zone <- as.data.frame(st_coordinates(point_zones))
coords_zone$name <- point_zones$NAME

coords_neighbor <- as.data.frame(st_coordinates(point_neighbors))
coords_neighbor$name <- point_neighbors$NAME

We add these labels to our final plot with geom_label_repel.

library(ggplot2)
library(ggthemes)
library(ggrepel)
library(scales)

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = ffxcounty, size = 0.2) +
  geom_sf(data = ffxcounty[ffxcounty$neighbor == 1, ], aes(fill = "#440154")) +
  geom_sf(data = ffxcounty[ffxcounty$opportunity == 1, ], aes(fill = "#FDE725"))  +
  geom_label_repel(data = coords_zone, aes(X, Y, label = name), 
                   colour = "black", nudge_x = 3, segment.size = 0.5) + 
  labs(title = "Fairfax County Opportunity Zones and Neighboring Tracts") +
  theme_map() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold"),
        legend.title = element_text(size = 11, face = "bold"),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 11),
        legend.position = c(0.1, 0.1)) +
  scale_fill_identity(name = "Tract Type", guide = "legend", 
                      labels = c("Neighboring Tract", "Opportunity Zone"))
